gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput

Class RRPRingFileInputer

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.DataSource
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.RRPRingFileInputer

  • public class RRPRingFileInputer
extends DataSource
    RRPRingFileInputer.java - This read data from an input ring file where the status is kept in a static ram disk safer RRPState file rather than the first block of the file. This changes was made due to the known problem of to many write cycles on static RAM disks causing failures of the media. This is a descendant of the RingFileInputer which used the first block method. Created on March 3, 2007, 1:48 PM

      • getNextData

        public int getNextData(byte[] buf,
              RRPRingFile rf)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Get the next data block, this returns -1 if there is no next block so caller can take other actions. It checks the RRPRingFile memory queue for the block first so most times the file is not actually read for current data
        Parameters:
        buf - buffer to receive the data bloc,
        rf - If not null, this is the RRPRingFile that is writing the ring file (called from within the same EdgeMom)
        Returns:
        -1 if no data is available, -2 if file is closed, else the length of the MiniSEED block returned.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
